
List DVB tuner devices

Usage: tslsdvb [options]

Options:

  -a N
  --adapter N
      Specifies the Nth DVB adapter in the system. This option can be used
      instead of device name.

  --debug[=level]
      Produce debug traces. The default level is 1. Higher levels produce more
      messages.

  -d name
  --device-name name
      Specify the DVB receiver device name. This is a DirectShow/BDA tuner
      filter name (not case sensitive, blanks are ignored). By default, the
      first DVB receiver device is used. Use the tslsdvb utility to list all
      DVB devices.

  -e
  --enumerate-devices
      Legacy option, equivalent to --test enumerate-devices.

  --help
      Display this help text.

  -t name
  --test name
      Run a specific DirectShow test. Very verbose output, for debug only. The
      default is none.
      Must be one of "bda-tuners", "enumerate-devices", "none",
      "tuning-spaces".

  -v
  --verbose
      Produce verbose output.

  --version
      Display the TSDuck version number.

